{"key":"processedPost-9789546","value":{"id":9789546,"first":9789480,"last":9789929,"when":1234539114,"utime":"02/13/09 05:31 PM","content":"I've used instant coffee before.&nbsp; It works fine.&nbsp; Decaf works as well as regular coffee too, if that's what you have.<br /><br />Normally what I do is every morning when I make a pot of coffee, I take the leftover liquid coffee that's in the pot from the day before, and pour it into an empty coffee can, which I then put in the freezer.&nbsp; Once full, it's the right amount to soak a large batch of grains.&nbsp; Keeping it frozen prevents mold from growing on it.<br /><br />For bulk substrates, you can usually get all the free coffee grinds you want from local restaurants or coffee shops.<br />RR","title":"Re: Just as good as the real thing... I think.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}